                <p class="name">MANCHESTER UNITED ANNOUNCES PRE-SEASON TOUR IN CHINA</p>
                <div class="images">
                    <img src="http://worldsoccertalk.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/man-united-china-2016-tour.jpg" alt="" />
                    <img src="http://images.thepeoplesperson.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/23074608/tour2016.jpg" alt="" />
                </div>
                <div class="news-item-content">
                    <p class="title"></p>
                    <p>
                        Manchester United have announced that they will travel to China this summer on their pre-season tour.
                        They will play two games - including a derby against Manchester City in the International Champions Cup.
                        They will face Manchester City in Beijing on Monday, July 25 They will also play Borussia Dortmund in Shanghai on Friday, July 22 .
                        The new Premier League season is set to begin on Saturday, August 13.
                        The eight-day tour forms part of United’s preparations for the 2016-17 Premier League season.
                        They are set to announce further dates and, venues and ticket details.
                        United's pre-season tour games are usually screened live on MUTV.
                        Speaking ahead of the tour, United’s Executive Vice Chairman, Ed Woodward, said: “Manchester United has strong historical links with China and we are very proud of our relationship and of our fans throughout the country.
                        “A total of almost 500,000 supporters have attended previous games during our visits to China and we have always enjoyed exceptional support in the country, so naturally it is something that everybody is very much looking forward to this summer.”
                        The game against City will be the highlight for many fans - especially if Jose Mourinho is appointed Louis van Gaal’s successor and comes up against his old rival Pep Guardiola.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
